  <title>TEMPORARY FULL TIME/PART-TIME TEACHING ASSISTANTS / DEMONSTRATORS IN URBAN AND REGIONAL PLANNING (1 POSITION)</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/temporary-full-timepart-time-teaching-assistants-demonstrators-urban-and-regional-planning-1-0</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;TEMPORARY FULL TIME/PART-TIME TEACHING ASSISTANTS / DEMONSTRATORS IN URBAN AND REGIONAL PLANNING (1 POSITION)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;a title="View user profile." href="https://www.ub.bw/user/1558" lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/1558" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" class="username" xml:lang=""&gt;ramahobok&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Tue, 15/08/2023 - 09:44&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Architecture and Planning&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF ENGINEERING AND TECHNOLOGY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF ARCHITECTURE AND PLANNING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;TEMPORARY FULL TIME/PART-TIME TEACHING ASSISTANTS / DEMONSTRATORS IN URBAN AND REGIONAL PLANNING (1 POSITION)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FET/A&amp;P05/2023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Successful candidates will be required to assist with the Planning Studios, Planning Techniques and Theoretical courses, practical, labs and tutorials in Urban and Regional Planning and carry out any other duties assigned by the HOD.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants must have: (i) a minimum of 4-year B.A. or B.S c. Degree in Urban and Regional Planning, Urban Design or any equivalent discipline; (ii) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;A minimum of 2(ii) or a GPA of 3 on a 5-point scale. (iii) Applicants with a Degree in Urban and Regional Planning should&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; have an average pass of 65% in Planning Studios; (iv) experience with GIS, CAD and design techniques at inter-mediate level (v) Membership of PITP/RTPI or any other recognized professional body will be an added advantage. A minimum of one year university teaching experience or two years of professional practice will be an added advantage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisted applicants may be called for interview where they will present their portfolios.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Letters of applications are to address the stated qualifications and provide any other information to assist the University to determine your suitability for the position. You should quote the vacancy number of the post applied for; provide current CV (including telephone and telefax numbers and email addresses); certified true copies of educational certificates, transcripts and THREE (3) reference letters. Send your application to: &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Engineering and Technology, University of Botswana, Private Bag UB 0061Gaborone, Botswana. Telephone: (267) 3554214 Fax: (267) 3952309 Email: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:recruitmentfet@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;recruitmentfet@ub.ac.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;   &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; (i) Quote the Vacancy Number(s) and Position(s) applied for and (ii) submit their references directly to the above address, before the stipulated closing date. Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be acknowledged.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to &lt;strong&gt;Office No. 255 Block 248 (FET Building).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB: Only short-listed applicants will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open until filled&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

